FBIS4-64004 "drsov103_a_94026" FBIS-SOV-94-103 Daily Report 26 May 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Moscow To Appeal to UN Over Fighting in Bosnia Moscow To Appeal to UN Over Fighting in Bosnia LD2605151694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1401 GMT 26 May 94 LD2605151694 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Boris Krivoshey and Aleksandr Krylovich] [Text] Moscow May 26 TASS -- Russia's representative at the United Nations was instructed to appeal to the U.N. Security Council, initiating a discussion of military operations which are being carried out by the Bosnian Government Army against Bosnian Serbs, said director of the Press and Information Department of the Russian Foreign Ministry, Georgiy Karasin, at a briefing held here today. "The aim of the Russian diplomacy is to prevent further deterioration of the situation in Bosnia-Herzegovina as a whole," the Russian diplomat said. "Russia is particularly concerned about an unstable situation around Tuzla, Moslem refusal to join the agreement on a safe area of Gorazde and increased shelling of the area of Brsko controlled by the Serbs," the Russian diplomat said.
